name: Cumbuco
description: Cumbuco is a world-class kitesurfing destination with consistent cross-shore winds and flat water lagoons.

name: Dakhla
description: Dakhla offers perfect flat water conditions in its lagoon and consistent winds almost year-round.

name: Essaouira
description: Essaouira is known as the 'Wind City of Africa' with strong trade winds and a mix of flat water and wave conditions.

name: Fuerteventura
description: Fuerteventura is one of the Canary Islands' best kitesurfing destinations, with consistent winds and various spots for different skill levels.

name: Kalpitiya
description: Kalpitiya offers flat water lagoons and consistent winds during the main season, making it a growing kitesurfing destination.

name: Langebaan
description: Langebaan Lagoon offers flat water and consistent winds, making it one of the best kitesurfing spots in South Africa.

name: Le Morne
description: Le Morne offers a variety of conditions from flat water to waves, with a beautiful backdrop of the Le Morne Brabant mountain.

name: Leucate
description: Leucate is one of the windiest spots in France, hosting the annual Mondial du Vent kitesurfing competition.

name: Maui (Kite Beach)
description: Kite Beach in Maui offers consistent trade winds and is one of the most popular kitesurfing spots in Hawaii.

name: Mui Ne
description: Mui Ne is known for its strong and consistent winds during the dry season, making it a popular kitesurfing destination in Southeast Asia.

name: Paracas
description: Paracas offers strong, consistent winds and is becoming increasingly popular among kitesurfers in South America.

name: Boracay
description: Boracay's Bulabog Beach is known for its consistent winds and flat water conditions during the amihan season.

name: Hood River
description: Hood River is known for its strong thermal winds during summer and beautiful scenery in the Columbia River Gorge.

name: Jericoacoara
description: Jericoacoara (Jeri) is a world-renowned kitesurfing destination with consistent winds and a unique setting in a national park.

name: Koh Phangan
description: Koh Phangan offers good kitesurfing conditions during the northeast monsoon season, with several beaches suitable for the sport.

name: La Ventana
description: La Ventana is known for its consistent winter winds and is a popular destination for kitesurfers from North America.

name: Prea
description: Prea offers consistent cross-shore winds and is less crowded than nearby Jericoacoara, making it a favorite among kitesurfers.

name: Zanzibar
description: Zanzibar offers consistent trade winds and beautiful beaches, making it a great kitesurfing destination in East Africa.

name: Cabarete
description: Cabarete is known as the kiteboarding capital of the Caribbean, offering consistent trade winds and warm water year-round.
